CFS Memory Manager Configuration Parameters

CFS Memory Manager Commands CFS Memory Manager Telemetry CFS Memory Manager Table Definitions

The following are configuration parameters used to configure the CFS Memory Manager Application either for each platform or for a mission as a whole.

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_DATA_SEG
Maximum number of bytes per dump data segment

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_FILE_DATA_EEPROM
Maximum number of bytes for a file dump from EEPROM memory

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_FILE_DATA_MEM16
Maximum number of bytes for a file dump from MEM16 memory

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_FILE_DATA_MEM32
Maximum number of bytes for a file dump from MEM32 memory

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_FILE_DATA_MEM8
Maximum number of bytes for a file dump from MEM8 memory

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_FILE_DATA_RAM
Maximum number of bytes for a file dump from RAM memory

Global MM_MAX_DUMP_FILE_DATA_SYMTBL
Maximum number of bytes for a symbol table file dump

Global MM_MAX_FILL_DATA_EEPROM
Maximum number of bytes for a fill to EEPROM memory

Global MM_MAX_FILL_DATA_MEM16
Maximum number of bytes for a fill to MEM16 memory

Global MM_MAX_FILL_DATA_MEM32
Maximum number of bytes for a fill to MEM32 memory

Global MM_MAX_FILL_DATA_MEM8
Maximum number of bytes for a fill to MEM8 memory

Global MM_MAX_FILL_DATA_RAM
Maximum number of bytes for a fill to RAM memory

Global MM_MAX_FILL_DATA_SEG
Maximum number of bytes per fill data segment

Global MM_MAX_LOAD_DATA_SEG
Maximum number of bytes per load data segment

Global MM_MAX_LOAD_FILE_DATA_EEPROM
Maximum number of bytes for a file load to EEPROM memory

Global MM_MAX_LOAD_FILE_DATA_MEM16
Maximum number of bytes for a file load to MEM16 memory

Global MM_MAX_LOAD_FILE_DATA_MEM32
Maximum number of bytes for a file load to MEM32 memory

Global MM_MAX_LOAD_FILE_DATA_MEM8
Maximum number of bytes for a file load to MEM8 memory

Global MM_MAX_LOAD_FILE_DATA_RAM
Maximum number of bytes for a file load to RAM memory

Global MM_MAX_UNINTERRUPTABLE_DATA
Maximum number of bytes for an uninterruptable load

Global MM_MISSION_REV
Mission specific version number for MM application

Global MM_OPT_CODE_MEM16_MEMTYPE
Optional MEM16 compile switch

Global MM_OPT_CODE_MEM32_MEMTYPE
Optional MEM32 compile switch

Global MM_OPT_CODE_MEM8_MEMTYPE
Optional MEM8 compile switch

Global MM_PROCESSOR_CYCLE
Segment break processor delay
